{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"diss-ale-jet","description":"# BUG: MCP run_workflow bypasses REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM for v3 branch/loop/map LLM steps\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. On a write-enabled MCP server with `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` unset, call `run_workflow(\"plan-review\", <ticket>)`.\n2. Observe the ALLOW_LLM fence (`mcp_server.py:946`) is skipped and billable single-turn finder calls fire.\n\nRoot cause: `has_llm_steps._scan` (`src/rebar/llm/workflow/runs.py:285-308`) flattens a v3 branch\nstep's `{when, then:[...], else:[...]}` dict via `list(values())`, so the bare-array arms become\nlist items that are skipped by `if not isinstance(s, dict): continue`. Empirically `has_llm_steps`\nreturns **False** for both `gates/plan-review.yaml` and `gates/completion-verification.yaml` (their\nLLM steps live only inside branch arms), while `code-review.yaml` (top-level LLM steps) returns True.\n\nExpected: `has_llm_steps` returns True for any workflow with an LLM step nested in a v3 branch/loop/map arm.\nActual: returns False -> the documented billing/policy gate is bypassed on default-shipped gates.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `_scan` descends into bare-array arms (v3 `then`/`else`/`body`) after flattening.\n- [ ] Regression test asserts True for a minimal v3 branch-with-LLM-arm AND for the shipped\n      `plan-review.yaml` + `completion-verification.yaml` gates.\n- [ ] `make lint` + the workflow test suite pass; commit carries a `rebar-ticket:` trailer.","id":"ce94-8621-497a-4528","parent_id":"9322-f84a-e047-4471","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"BUG: run_workflow bypasses REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM for v3 branch/loop/map LLM steps"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783053681042146001,"uuid":"e2d97557-df79-4ae6-b176-f6b68f9fc38b"}